\subsection{The Dependent Function Type}
This is very similar to the non-dependent case. The difference is we must substitute into $B$.
If
\[ \prov \Gamma \rctx \qquad \Gamma^\ominus \prov A : \rtype \qquad \Gamma^\ominus, x : \wid A \prov B : \rtype \qquad
\Gamma, \star \prov f : (x : \wid A) \to B\]
then there exists an explicit isomorphism
\[\Gamma \prov \pp f {(x : \wid A) \to B}  \cong (a :  A) (a' : \pp { a} A) \to \pp {f\ a} {[\epair a {a'} / x]B} \]

